name: maize grain, feed to generic market for energy feed | protein feed, 100% crude | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20576/documentation

This activity is a linking activity, i.e. it connects maize grain, feed with generic market for energy feed in South Africa. Maize grain, feed is used primarily as a feed for animals, thus traded on generic feed market with other energy- containing products.

The activity starts with the reception of maize grain, feed.

This linking activity has the maize grain, feed as an input and protein and energy feed as outputs.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds

exchanges.description: Calculated based on literature values for "maize grain" (Feedipedia, 2019), which reports a crude protein content of 17.3% of dry matter and a gross energy content equates to 18.7 MJ/kg dry matter of fed, with a dry matter content equates 86.3% of fed. Reference: Feedipedia (2019) Maize Grain, Animal feed resources information system, Available at: https://www.feedipedia.org/node/556. (Accessed January 2018)
